In late [[Mirtul]] of the {{yearlinkName|1479}}, Delasko Sornstern was one of the guests at the [[Open Feast]], spending much time with his close associates Broryn Windstag and Kathkote Dawntard.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|68|6}}

Sornstern was with Broryn Windstag and Kathkote Dawntard when the three of them entered, drunk, to the [[Dragonriders Club]], started a brawl, and attacked [[Delnor]] a palace messenger there, almost fighting [[Arclath Delcastle]].{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|217-221|21}} They were later repelled by the arrival of the city watch of [[Suzail]],{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|225-226|21}} and interrogated by the [[War Wizards]].{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|230-231|22}}

After the meeting, they fled towards Marlin Stormserpent's residence at [[Stormserpent Towers]], who involved them at that time in his intrigues involving ''[[blueflame item]]s''.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|265-266|25}}

Later, the young lords Dawntard, Sornstern and Windstag carried out a frantic search for the axe; so energetic and haphazard their search was, that they themselves expressly did not understand the intensity of their own actions.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|326-327|31}} Among other actions during their search, they'd offered large amounts of coin in a number of taverns frequented by the nobility, including [[the Rose and Dragon]], [[the Servant Exalted]], and [[the Hrelto]].{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|331-332|32}} They were unknowingly controlled by the [[vampire]] [[archmage]] [[Manshoon]], who had them target Lord [[Barandror Murandrake]]'s residence, where they finally found the axe.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|334-335|32}}  Though they were pursued by the War Wizard [[Glathra Barcantle]] and Swordcaptain [[Dralkin]] along the way, and nearly ran out of breath, a spell whisked them away, teleporting them nearly all the way to Stormserpent Towers.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|337-338|32}} After delivering the axe to Marlin Stormserpent, they fainted.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|340|32}}

After the [[Council of the Dragon]], Lord Delasko Sornstern had a brief talk with [[Broryn Windstag]] about his father Haedro's learnings about [[blueflame item]]s and [[the Imprisoners]]. Unknown to them, they were being spied on by the [[highknight]] Sir [[Talonar Winter]].
